Vimal Manohar received his B.Tech degree in electrical engineering from the Indian Institute of Technology Madras, India in 2013. He is currently at the Center for Language and Speech Processing and pursuing the PhD degree in electrical engineering at the Johns Hopkins University, Baltimore, MD. His research interests lie in the general area of speech recognition with special focus on semi-supervised training of acoustic and language models, and speech segmentation. He is an active developer of the open-source Kaldi speech recognition toolkit, which is widely used for speech technology research and applications.

